title: Mount Everest Climbers Must Now Meet This New Requirement
description: Mount Everest climbers must now rent and wear a tracking device to make search and rescue missions easier, per reports.

title: Ship Hit by Yemen’s Houthi Rebels Sinks in the Red Sea, Marking First Vessel Lost in Conflict
description: A ship attacked by Yemen's Houthi rebels has sunk in the Red Sea after days of taking on water, officials said on Saturday.

title: How World Leaders Have Reacted to the Deaths of People In Gaza Waiting For an Aid Convoy
description: World leaders are putting pressure on Israel to allow in more humanitarian aid to Gaza, with some turning to their own efforts to do so.

title: Is Biden ‘Too Old’? Voters to View State of the Union Speech as Crucial Test
description: Voters will watch Biden's performance closely amid concerns about his age.

title: Do the Right Thing, America
description: We Ukrainians have spent two years courageously defending ourselves against Russian aggression. America must not be tempted to abandon us.

title: How Online Adoption Ads Prey on Pregnant People
description: "It’s difficult to overstate how captivated many mothers are by the adoptive family profiles they find online," writes Gretchen Sisson.

title: Severe Storm In California and Nevada Shuts Interstate, Leaves Thousands Without Power
description: A blizzard raged overnight in the Sierra Nevada. The biggest storm of the season shut down a stretch of Interstate-80 in California.

title: Fashion Icon Iris Apfel Dies Aged 102
description: Iris Apfel, a textile expert, interior designer and fashion celebrity known for her eccentric style, has died aged 102.

title: Yogurt Can Now Claim It May Reduce the Risk of Diabetes
description: The FDA decided to grant the food a qualified health claim.

title: RSV Vaccine May Be Linked to a Slightly Higher Risk of Guillain-Barre Syndrome
description: Officials are investigating whether there's a link between two new RSV vaccines and cases of a rare nervous system disorder in older adults.
